  "prompt": "Which is the best website or a portal to read Tamil literature?",
  "response": "There are several websites and portals where you can read Tamil literature online. Some of the notable ones include:\n\n1. **Project Madurai**: An open, voluntary initiative to digitize and freely distribute ancient Tamil literature. You can visit [Project Madurai](http://www.projectmadurai.org) for a collection of classical Tamil literary works.\n\n2. **Tamil Literature Collections**: Sites like [TamizhBooks](https://www.tamizhbooks.com) and [TamilCube](https://www.tamilcube.com) offer various collections of Tamil literature, including classical and modern works.\n\n3. **Sangam Literature**: For ancient Tamil literature like Sangam poetry, [Tamil Virtual Academy](http://www.tamilvu.org) provides a wealth of resources and texts.\n\n4. **Digital Library of India**: This website hosts a multitude of resources in various languages, including Tamil literature. You can access it at [Digital Library of India](https://www.dli.gov.in).\n\n5. **Tamil-culture.com**: Offers articles, essays, and literary pieces related to Tamil culture and literature. Visit [Tamil Culture](https://www.tamilculture.com) for more insights.\n\nEach of these websites provides access to different types of Tamil literary works, ranging from ancient texts to modern writings. Choose one based on your specific interest in the type and period of Tamil literature you wish to explore.",
